                  <p class="content-xD6dy1 margin-left-rhxaL1 line-height-9Qkso4 padding-FBkWQ3 margin-FBkWQ3">The Swift language has grown over the years and become more and more powerful. It now boosts a comprehensive static type system (generics, existentials…), a suite of concurrency tools (actors, dynamic isolation…), and most recently even ownership capabilities (consuming, borrowing, non-copyable types…). In “Back to basics” we will focus on just one part of the language in order to uncover the deep theory behind that feature as well as provide concrete advice for writing real-world code.
                  </p>

              </pf-markdown>
